"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of churn likelihood based on satisfaction scores, churn scores, CLTV, and customer status. Next, the user brushes and selects risk categories in View 1 for filtering purposes, impacting View 2's box plot distribution across demographics. Then the user clicks specific demographic categories in View 2 and gains detailed insights into specific clusters in View 3 at the [Detail] level using a parallel coordinates chart. Lastly, View 4 at the [Insight] level displays aggregated findings on churn risk factors grouped into actionable risk categories in a heatmap."